PhD students get brief overview about the newest scientific literature in bioorganic chemistry.  Every seminar bases on a recently published scientific paper presented by a student. First, the presenter gives short wider overview about the problem. Then the experimental and theoretical part of the paper will be critically analyzed and conclusion about the weak and strong sides of the paper will be discussed. Seminars take place in English. This gives students experience to present scientific results and to perform scientific discussions in English.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Give experience to PhD students in critical reading of new scientific publications in bioorganic chemistry. Students get experience in presentation of critical review of scientific data in seminar and perform scientific discussion in English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who passed the course successfully: - knows at least particularly newest scientific literature in his/her study field connected with bioorganic chemistry - is able to present and analyze data given in particular scientific paper and connect this with his/her own project - is able to perform critical analysis of data presented in scientific paper; Finding weak and strong sides of the paper and present these in seminar presentation in English - has experience of scientific discussions in English.
